​1. Information Collection and Use
​GLive is built with a strict zero-data-collection infrastructure. * No Personal Data: The Application does not collect, track, store, or transmit any personally identifiable information (such as your name, email address, phone number, or device identifiers).
​No Cloud Backups / No Persistence: Absolutely no data leaves your device. All application configurations and dynamic parameters are kept strictly inside the application's private local cache. Because no data is synced to any external server or cloud service, if you uninstall and reinstall the Application, all of your previous settings and local configurations are permanently gone and cannot be recovered.
​2. Device Permissions
​To provide live streaming capabilities, the Application requires access to specific hardware components. These permissions are used solely in real-time on your device and are never monitored or recorded by us:
​Camera: Required to capture video for your live streams.
​Microphone (Audio): Required to capture audio for your live streams.
​3. Third-Party Services & Streaming Destinations
​When you use GLive to broadcast to third-party platforms (such as YouTube via RTMP), your stream data goes directly from your device's camera/microphone to the destination ingest server specified by you. We do not intermediate, cache, log, or have access to your live stream feeds or your stream keys. Your use of third-party streaming destinations is governed solely by those platforms' respective privacy policies and terms of service.
​4. Children’s Privacy
​Since the Application does not collect any information whatsoever from any user, we do not knowingly or unknowingly collect any data from children under the age of 13.
​5. Changes to This Privacy Policy
​We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
​6. Contact Us
